<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="C33.S19">
<title>Power-Series Expansions in <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.m1">r</Math></title>          
<para xml:id="C33.S19.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="33.19.1" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S19.E1">f\left(\epsilon,\ell;r\right)=r^{\ell+1}\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\alpha_{k}r^{k},</Math> where <Math equation-number="33.19.2" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S19.E2">\alpha_{0}=2^{\ell+1}/(2\ell+1)!,\alpha_{1}=-\alpha_{0}/(\ell+1),k(k+2\ell+1)\alpha_{k}+2\alpha_{k-1}+\epsilon\alpha_{k-2}=0, if k=2,3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="33.19.3" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S19.E3">2\pi h\left(\epsilon,\ell;r\right)={\sum_{k=0}^{2\ell}\frac{(2\ell-k)!\gamma_{ k}}{k!}(2r)^{k-\ell}-\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\delta_{k}r^{k+\ell+1}}-A(\epsilon, \ell)\left(2\ln|2r/\kappa|+\Re\psi\left(\ell+1+\kappa\right)+\Re\psi\left(- \ell+\kappa\right)\right){f\left(\epsilon,\ell;r\right),} if r\neq 0.</Math>
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.s3">
Here <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.m1">\kappa</Math> is defined by (33.14.6),
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.s4">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.m2">A(\epsilon,\ell)</Math> is defined by (33.14.11) or (33.14.12),
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.s5">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.m3">\gamma_{0}=1</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.m4">\gamma_{1}=1</Math> , and <Math equation-number="33.19.4" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S19.E4">\gamma_{k}-\gamma_{k-1}+\tfrac{1}{4}(k-1)(k-2\ell-2)\epsilon\gamma_{k-2}=0, if k=2,3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.s6">
Also, <Math equation-number="33.19.5" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S19.E5">\delta_{0}=\left(\beta_{2\ell+1}-2(\psi\left(2\ell+2\right)+\psi\left(1\right) )A(\epsilon,\ell)\right)\alpha_{0},\delta_{1}=\left(\beta_{2\ell+2}-2(\psi\left(2\ell+3\right)+\psi\left(2\right) )A(\epsilon,\ell)\right)\alpha_{1},</Math> <Math equation-number="33.19.6" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S19.E6">k(k+2\ell+1)\delta_{k}+2\delta_{k-1}+\epsilon\delta_{k-2}+2(2k+2\ell+1)A( \epsilon,\ell)\alpha_{k}=0, if k=2,3,\dots,</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.m5">\beta_{0}=\beta_{1}=0</Math> , and <Math equation-number="33.19.7" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S19.E7">\beta_{k}-\beta_{k-1}+\tfrac{1}{4}(k-1)(k-2\ell-2)\epsilon\beta_{k-2}+\tfrac{1 }{2}(k-1)\epsilon\gamma_{k-2}=0, if k=2,3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.s7">
The expansions (33.19.1) and (33.19.3) converge for all finite values of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.m6">r</Math> , except <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S19.p1.m7">r=0</Math> in the case of (33.19.3).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</section>
